Saglam GYO Gets Approval to Merge With Real Estate Developer Saf

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-09-26T07:39:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/saglam-gyo-gets-approval-to-merge-with-real-estate-developer-saf.html
Saglam Gayrimenkul Yatirim
Ortakligi AS (SAGYO) , a Turkish real estate investment trust owned by
food group Yıldız Holding AS, got approval from the market
regulator for a merger by taking over real estate developer
Saf Gayrimenkul Gelistirme Insaat & Ticaret AS.  Saglam GYO also got approval to increase its capital to
886.6 million liras ($480 million) from 56 million liras as a
result of the merger, the company said in a statement to the
 Istanbul Stock Exchange  today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Aydan Eksin at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net  